Fantastic idea and easy to execute. I used emmenthaler and fontina in a 3-lb. red kuri squash and it was divine. Eyeballed the liquids at a 50/50 ratio just till I could see it peaking through the mounds of bread and cheese. Baked at 350 for two hours. The squash split about 45 minutes into it, but if this happens to you, don't despair: you really don't need the liquid you'll lose, and any cheese/bread that pours out will get lovely and crunchy and brown. Loved those parts so much I put the whole thing back minus the top and broiled it for 5 minutes to crisp up the rest. Perfect fall/winter meal, especially with a side of prosciutto and a good mustard.

